br>3rd 2 lines:<br><span class=\"quote\">&gt;10. If God were to exist, He would be willing and able to prevent evil. (from 3 and 9)<\/span><br><span class=\"quote\">&gt;11. If God were willing and able to prevent evil, evil would not exist.<\/span><br><span class=\"quote\">&gt;12. There is evil.<\/span><br>Begs the question; &quot;evil&quot; is never defined. If evil just means &quot;consciously causing suffering or harm,&quot; then premise 5 begs the question, and thus the conclusion to this syllogism doesn&#039;t follow.<br>Whatever &quot;evil&quot; means, the argument has to show it to exist, and to be incompatible with omnibenevolence.<br><span class=\"quote\">&gt;13. God doesn&#039;t exist<\/span><br><br>Last 2 lines add nothing new and are irrelevant.","filename":"1490560738684[1]","ext":".jpg","w":613,"h":412,"tn_w":250,"tn_h":168,"tim":1490563135907,"time":1490563135,"md5":"zMlDGhSg7tZERXGtdp7GIQ==","fsize":154203,"resto":0,"id":"FHXZ4pMr","country":"US","bumplimit":0,"imagelimit":0,"semantic_url":"1st-2-lines-are-equivalent-to","country_name":"United States","replies":1,"images":0,"unique_ips":2},{"no":118417773,"now":"03\/26\/17(Sun)17:23:10","name":"Anonymous","com":"<a href=\"#p118417209\" class=\"quotelink\">&gt;&gt;118417209<\/a><br>3rd and 4th lines are illogical absurdities<br><br><br> God is omnipotent and grants man autonomy.. His limited intervention is not malevolence.. the evil in this world is the result of the actions of mankind not God. <br><br>Accusing God of malevolence for mankind&#039;s deeds is absurd.","time":1490563390,"resto":118417209,"id":"ACGlTVH6","country":"US","country_name":"United States"}]}